ETHICAL USE NOTICE

k-Terminus is designed for legitimate system administration of machines you
own or have explicit authorization to manage.

INTENDED USE CASES:
- Managing personal machines across networks
- Remote development and system administration
- Accessing home lab servers from anywhere
- Team collaboration on authorized systems

THIS SOFTWARE SHOULD NOT BE USED FOR:
- Unauthorized access to computer systems
- Deploying agents on machines without owner consent
- Any activity that violates applicable computer access laws
- Malware distribution or command-and-control of compromised systems

The authors do not condone and are not responsible for any misuse of this
software. Users are solely responsible for ensuring their use complies with
all applicable laws and regulations.

Unauthorized access to computer systems is illegal in most jurisdictions,
including but not limited to:
- Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (United States)
- Computer Misuse Act (United Kingdom)
- Criminal Code sections on unauthorized computer access (Canada, EU, etc.)
